      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Switching from sertraline to St. John's wort without consulting your doctor is not advisable. Sertraline is a prescription medication, and abruptly stopping it can lead to withdrawal symptoms. St. John's wort can interact with sertraline, potentially reducing its effectiveness or causing adverse effects. It's essential to discuss any changes with your healthcare provider to ensure safe and effective treatment.",
